Your organization has been managing AWS infrastructure manually through the AWS Console. You have been tasked with bringing existing infrastructure under Terraform management.
The following resources already exist in your AWS account in the ap-south-1 region (region may be different in the actual exam):

A Bastion Host EC2 instance used for SSH access
A Launch Template named MyTemplate used to define instance configuration
An Auto Scaling Group named testASG using the above Launch Template
You must import all these resources into Terraform state, ensure configuration is dynamically driven (no hardcoded values where avoidable), 
and apply appropriate lifecycle rules to prevent Terraform from overriding runtime scaling decisions.



