Task 3 — Apply Lifecycle Rule to Auto Scaling Group
The Auto Scaling Group currently has desired_capacity = 1 in both the Terraform config and in AWS. 
Your team wants to document a scale-out intent of desired_capacity = 2 in the Terraform code, but must not allow Terraform to enforce this value on every apply, 
since the Auto Scaling service manages capacity dynamically at runtime.
Change desired_capacity from 1 to 2 in the aws_autoscaling_group.example resource block
Add an appropriate lifecycle block so that Terraform ignores any changes made to desired_capacity
Run terraform plan — it must show No changes. Your infrastructure matches the configuration.
